    android demo MASTG-TEST-0272

    MASTG-DEMO-0051: Identifying Insecure Dependencies through SBOM Creation

    Download MASTG-DEMO-0051 APK Open MASTG-DEMO-0051 Folder Build MASTG-DEMO-0051 APK

    Steps¶

    Execute cdxgen in the root directory of the Android Studio project.

    run.sh
    1
    cdxgen -t java -o sbom.json

    This will create a SBOM file that can be uploaded to dependency-track by following Software Composition Analysis (SCA) of Android Dependencies by Creating a SBOM.

    Observation¶

    In the project of dependency-track, where the SBOM has been uploaded, the scan should have identified over 200 unique dependencies (components) with 7 vulnerable dependencies and 7 vulnerabilities (as more vulnerabilities might be found over time this number might increase).

    sbom.json
